FROM crop_cycles 
WHERE created_by = 'admin';

external_knowledge:
- Crop damage is a critical metric in agriculture; 
- The 2023 growing season refers to the specific time of the year when crops are grown and harvested in 2023;
- Pesticide use categories (e.g., none, low, moderate, high) indicate the level of pesticide application;
- Soil types (e.g., sandy, clay) and crop types (e.g., corn, soybeans) are essential factors in determining pesticide use and crop damage.

